## Website direction

The site structure follows good service-business practice by clearly stating what you do, who you help, what services you offer, and how people can contact you. The portfolio planning also follows recommended service-business portfolio structure by emphasizing project context, problem, approach, deliverables, and results rather than just showing visuals. [mailerlite](https://www.mailerlite.com/blog/web-pages-a-website-should-have)

## How to use Step 5

Use the homepage copy for your landing page, the services copy for a dedicated services page or section, the founder profile for your About page, and the portfolio list to start building proof even if some examples begin as demo case studies. For a solo business, this gives you a practical minimum website system that can later expand with FAQ, blog, privacy policy, and more case studies. [nicepage](https://nicepage.com/k/consulting-one-page-template)

